{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778547819,"nonce":"0h6AZJXEvbmjJ6VAR8JSafIOE88=","message":"**Analysis complete** — see commit ceb3b87 on feature/lit-replication-results.\n\n## Results — primary metric (vel-RMSE ratio)\n\n| Cell | Vel-RMSE-ratio | Pos-RMSE-ratio | CV (peak vel) | Mean PV (m/s) | Hold drift (mm) | TTP |\n|------|---------------:|---------------:|--------------:|--------------:|----------------:|----:|\n| lit__flat_jerk        | 1.157 | 1.293 | 0.092 | 0.590 | **22.9** | 62.4 |\n| lit__post_jerk        | 1.229 | 1.235 | 0.040 | 0.791 | 3.3 | 71.8 |\n| lit__full_jerk        | 1.239 | 1.233 | 0.041 | 0.791 | 3.4 | 71.8 |\n| lit__flat_nojerk      | **0.978** | 0.897 | 0.089 | 0.606 | **24.3** | 58.5 |\n| lit__post_nojerk      | 1.091 | 1.055 | 0.026 | 0.969 | 2.3 | 54.6 |\n| lit__full_nojerk      | 1.250 | 1.277 | 0.026 | 0.964 | 2.7 | 54.5 |\n\n## Decision\n\n**No cell beats the \u003c 0.5 vel-RMSE-ratio threshold.** Best cell is `lit__flat_nojerk` at 0.978 — still worse than the 2bc95fd prior best `gru__jerk` (0.758). 5 of 6 cells are above 1.0 (within-cell RMSE \u003e nearest-across-cell RMSE → replicates do not cluster).\n\n## Headline findings\n\n1. **Negative result for the lit-replication hypothesis.** Faithful C\u0026S Eq. 15 schedule (powerlaw, no jerk) does not produce tightly clustered replicates. Performs WORSE than the prior production loss baseline.\n2. **Schedule effect dominates jerk effect.** Within either jerk condition, flat schedule is the best for vel-RMSE-ratio; jerk on/off changes ratio by ≤ 15% within a schedule. Powerlaw schedule actively makes within-cell variance worse.\n3. **Universal hold-drift failure.** Every cell exceeds the 1 mm conditional-follow-up trigger:\n   - Flat cells: catastrophic 23-24 mm pre-go anticipation\n   - Powerlaw cells: 2.3-3.4 mm — better, but never reaches the \u003c 0.5 mm \"good hold\" threshold\n\n   **The conditional pre-go-mask follow-up matrix (`--nn-output-pre-go`) is unambiguously triggered.**\n4. **Powerlaw makes peak velocities too high** for no-jerk cells (0.96-0.97 m/s, above the 0.8 m/s sanity ceiling). Suggests the schedule encourages speeding up to fit late-trial targets rather than smoothing.\n\n## Within-schedule jerk effect\n\n| Schedule | Jerk on (vel-RMSE) | Jerk off (vel-RMSE) | Δ (off − on) |\n|----------|--------------------|---------------------|--------------|\n| Flat       | 1.157 | 0.978 | −0.179 (jerk-off BETTER) |\n| Post-go PL | 1.229 | 1.091 | −0.138 (jerk-off BETTER) |\n| Full-trial PL | 1.239 | 1.250 | +0.011 (tied) |\n\nContrary to Shahbazi expectation: jerk regulariser does NOT funnel replicates here.\n\n## Bugs surfaced and fixed in ceb3b87\n\n1. **run.json under-reports CLI flags.** `--nn-hidden-derivative 0.001` was actually used during training but the original run.json files omitted it. Recovered from `adversarial_model.eqx` hyperparams header (which IS complete) and confirmed via saved warmup_history TermTree weight at position 7. Each `results/f47abb1/runs/\u003ccell\u003e/run.json` now carries the recovered weight + a `cli_flags_reconstruction` field explaining provenance.\n2. **adversarial_model.eqx structure mismatch.** With `n_adversary_batches=0` the adversarial phase did not actually run, but `adversarial_model.eqx` was still saved with adversary state (`DisturbanceField.params_index.init.amplitude`) that does not match the local skeleton. Fix: analysis prefers `warmup_model.eqx` (same model weights for this matrix).\n\n## Conditional follow-up triggered\n\nPre-go-mask matrix follow-up will be filed as a new feature issue (under `c99ad9d` coord). Suggested design: revisit `--nn-output-pre-go` (starting weight 1e-2 per efc4d68) on the closest-to-threshold cell (`lit__post_jerk` or `lit__full_jerk`, vel-RMSE-ratio ~1.23). Goal: reduce hold drift below 0.5 mm without destroying clustering further.\n\n## Figures\n\n- `results/f47abb1/figures/rmse_ratio_comparison/` — Bar chart (PRIMARY)\n- `results/f47abb1/figures/peak_velocity_distributions/` — Violin/strip (CV annotated, auxiliary)\n- `results/f47abb1/figures/forward_velocity_profiles/` — Velocity time series per cell\n- `results/f47abb1/figures/hold_drift_profiles/` — Pre-go forward position (anticipation)\n- `results/f47abb1/figures/training_loss/` + `training_loss_per_term/` — Loss curves\n\nHTML renders at `_artifacts/f47abb1/figures/\u003ctopic\u003e/figure.html` (gitignored).","files":null}]}